Viktor Zuckerkandl (2 July 1896, Vienna – 5 April 1965, Locarno) was a Jewish-Austrian musicologist.
His doctorate was granted in 1927 from Vienna University, having earlier studied under Richard Robert.
He conducted freelance throughout the decade of the 1920s.
